# Palm Template — Design & Config Rules

This template is auto-deployed by the Ouro Portal. The portal generates `client.config.ts` and pushes it here on every deploy. Breaking the config contract breaks every live client site.

## The Contract: `src/types/client-config.ts`

This is the only file that connects the portal to the template. Rules:

- **Never remove or rename a field.** The portal will still send the old name and the site will break silently.
- **Never make an optional field required.** Config values can be null — always handle it.
- **Adding new optional fields is safe.** Use `field?: type | null` and provide a fallback in the component.

## Config Fields Reference

Key nullable fields the portal populates from intake + scrape data:

```ts
contact.address    // from intake form — may be null if not submitted
contact.hours      // from web scrape — may be null if not found
contact.emergency  // from web scrape — may be null if not found
contact.mapUrl     // auto-generated from address — null if no address
contact.phone      // from project record
contact.email      // from project record

reviews.score      // parsed from "4.8/5 på Google..." — may be null
reviews.count      // parsed from review string — fallback to "0"
reviews.show       // true if score or testimonials exist

trust.certifications  // string[] — may be empty []

about.stats        // { value, label }[] — may be empty []
about.teamSize     // may be null
about.founded      // may be null
```

## Component Rules

Always guard nullable fields before rendering:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — crashes if address is null
<p>{client.contact.address.toUpperCase()}</p>

// ✅ GOOD
{client.contact.address && <p>{client.contact.address}</p>}

// ✅ GOOD with fallback
<p>{client.contact.hours ?? "Kontakta oss för öppettider"}</p>
```

## What Is Safe to Edit

| Area | Safe? |
|---|---|
| Component layout, spacing, Tailwind classes | ✅ Yes |
| Typography, colors, gradients, shadows | ✅ Yes |
| Adding new sections that use existing config fields | ✅ Yes |
| Animations, hover states, transitions | ✅ Yes |
| `src/types/client-config.ts` — adding optional fields | ✅ Yes |
| `src/types/client-config.ts` — removing/renaming fields | ❌ No |
| `client.config.ts` — editing directly | ❌ No (overwritten on every deploy) |

## Data Flow (do not change)

```
Portal (assembleConfig) → pushes client.config.ts → GitHub → Vercel build
```

`client.config.ts` is overwritten every time the portal pushes a config update or deploys a new site. Any manual edits to it will be lost.
